-# Snipper
+# Bob Foreman ­ƒÅù´©Å
 
-The minimalist URL shortener.
+**Parallel orchestration for Bob CLI instances. Build faster by dividing work across isolated git worktrees.**
 
-## Features
+IBM Bob Coding Challenge 2026 submission by Team `ibm-hackathon-6`.
 
-- Six character random codes
-- Click analytics per link
-- History stored in localStorage
-- Dark mode UI
+---
 
+## Why Foreman
+
+**Problem:** Bob CLI works sequentially. Complex projects take hours when tasks could run in parallel.
+
+**Solution:** Bob Foreman spawns multiple Bob instances in isolated git worktrees, each handling a subtask. A central orchestrator estimates effort, distributes work, monitors progress, and merges results.
+
+**Result:** 4 workers built a complete URL shortener (Express backend, sql.js database, vanilla JS frontend) in **45 minutes**. Sequential execution would have taken ~9 hours.
+
+---
+
 ## Quick Start
 
-```bash
-npm install
-npm start
+```powershell
+# Estimate and spawn 4 parallel workers
+.\scripts\foreman-build.ps1 -TaskFile .foreman-prompts/readme.txt -Workers 4
+
+# Monitor progress
+Start-Process "http://localhost:8765/dashboard.html"
 ```
 
-Visit `localhost:3000` in browser.
+Workers run in `worktrees/<task-id>/`, isolated via git worktree. Status aggregated from `.foreman/tasks/*.json` and `logs/*.json`.
 
